02:49.728 --> 02:53.632
but we, we had agents
and different managers, uh

02:53.665 --> 02:56.801
who tried to see if they could penetrate

02:56.835 --> 02:59.904
the tangled web of our, of our career

02:59.938 --> 03:02.574
and most of them dropped out in horror.

03:02.607 --> 03:06.745
And we bumbled around America
playing raggedly.

03:06.778 --> 03:09.648
We started lookin',
uh, dirtier and dirtier

03:09.681 --> 03:11.983
and skinnier and skinnier

03:12.016 --> 03:13.652
and more and more used.

03:13.685 --> 03:15.554
And we were getting worse and worse.

03:15.587 --> 03:20.225
We're sinkin' fast
into semi-oblivious gigs.

03:20.259 --> 03:22.361
Some people still liked us.

03:22.394 --> 03:25.063
Some gigs I could
get it together to sing

03:25.096 --> 03:26.565
some I couldn't.

03:26.598 --> 03:29.668
Some gigs, I, we'd show up on time

03:29.701 --> 03:31.836
some we didn't.

03:31.870 --> 03:33.572
