04:41.606 --> 04:43.107
Nearly killed me, but you missed again

04:43.141 --> 04:45.844
so you have to keep trying next week.

04:47.278 --> 04:49.948
Leading up to the Michigan Palace job

04:49.981 --> 04:53.418
was, was, what I referred
to it as a death march.

04:53.452 --> 04:54.953
So they decided to book us

04:54.986 --> 04:58.289
in a little club outside of Detroit

04:58.323 --> 05:00.792
uh, called The Rock and Roll Farm.

05:00.825 --> 05:02.827
Turns out it's a biker bar.

05:02.861 --> 05:04.929
Here comes Iggy, out in the audience

05:04.963 --> 05:08.600
confronting people in-the,
uh-as only Iggy can do.

05:08.633 --> 05:10.469
And he comes up to one guy

05:10.502 --> 05:12.937
and the guy just hauls off

05:12.971 --> 05:15.106
and just cold-cocks him.

05:15.139 --> 05:16.274
Just, kaboom!

05:18.977 --> 05:20.311
I don't know how many of you

05:20.345 --> 05:23.382
saw us back in 1967

05:23.415 --> 05:24.783
when we first started, you know

05:24.816 --> 05:27.051
but it isn't too,
it isn't too easy being

05:27.085 --> 05:28.553
"The Stooges" sometimes, you know?

05:28.587 --> 05:29.954
Yeah!

05:29.988 --> 05:31.456
You know, after that gig

05:31.490 --> 05:32.891
nobody had to say anything.

05:32.924 --> 05:35.494
It was just, like, everybody had had it.

05:35.527 --> 05:37.028
I mean, we couldn't make a living.

05:37.061 --> 05:39.998
People were throwing shit at us
all the time

05:40.031 --> 05:42.467
and everybody was just tired of it.

05:42.501 --> 05:44.736
And so, so, uh..

05:44.769 --> 05:48.006
The-the brothers
moved back to Detroit.

05:48.039 --> 05:52.310
Jim never came to me and said it's over.

05:52.343 --> 05:54.078
I just figured it out myself.

05:54.112 --> 05:56.047
Well, here I am sleepin' on the floor

05:56.080 --> 05:59.484
I guess it's over.
I was basically homeless.

05:59.518 --> 06:01.252
I had a drum set.

06:01.285 --> 06:05.724
I sold it and bought
a one way ticket to Detroit.

06:07.526 --> 06:10.328
Ended up going over to mom's house

06:10.361 --> 06:12.564
and said, "Mom, I'm homeless

06:12.597 --> 06:15.266
I'm broke, I'm hungry."

06:15.299 --> 06:19.771
When the demise of
"The Stooges" occurred

06:19.804 --> 06:21.172
it wasn't really a surprise.

06:21.205 --> 06:24.342
And it goes back
to that full circle of, like

06:24.375 --> 06:27.211
go home, you know, to mom.

06:27.245 --> 06:28.847
After my brothers came home

06:28.880 --> 06:31.450
I remember feeling relieved

06:31.483 --> 06:33.084
and glad.

06:33.117 --> 06:35.687
It was like, phew. You know?

06:35.720 --> 06:37.956
They're safe.
That was the main thing.

06:37.989 --> 06:39.090
That they came home safe

06:39.123 --> 06:41.359
and they were still alive, you know?

06:41.392 --> 06:45.229
That's when I went home
to my parents' trailer.

06:45.263 --> 06:47.031
I was 24.

06:47.065 --> 06:49.400
And, um..

06:49.434 --> 06:52.971
The group had a... uh

06:53.004 --> 06:56.407
